#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:140
msgid "The whole pipeline rests on `haw.lock`. Two flags make it airtight in CI:"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:143
msgid "# fail unless haw.lock exists (no rev resolution)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:144
msgid "# assert tree == lock, exit 3 on drift\n"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:147
msgid ""
"`--locked` refuses to invent a lock on the fly — CI must build from the "
"_committed_ baseline, never resolve fresh. `verify` then proves the checkout "
"matches it. Together they guarantee the tree in CI is byte-for-byte the tree "
"you committed."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:151
msgid "📦 5. Distribution — publish what the fleet produced"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:153
msgid ""
"Once the fleet builds, `haw publish` uploads its artifacts to a generic/raw "
"artifact registry — **Nexus, Artifactory, GitLab, or Bitbucket**:"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:158
msgid "# print the plan, no creds, no network\n"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:161
msgid ""
"`--dry-run` prints exactly what _would_ upload (target, name, version, each "
"file) without touching the network or needing credentials — perfect for "
"wiring the step up safely first. Credentials come from the target's env vars "
"(e.g. `NEXUS_URL`, `NEXUS_USER`, `NEXUS_PASS`)."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:165
msgid "🔏 6. Signing, SBOM, and provenance — the supply chain"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:167
msgid ""
"This is where `haw` earns its keep for serious releases. Every signed "
"release ships with a `.sha256` checksum and a **keyless cosign signature** "
"(`.sig`/`.pem`) you can verify offline — even on an air-gapped host (see "
"[Installing hawser](../INSTALL.md))."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:171
msgid ""
"For _your_ fleet, the supply-chain features ship as the governance plugins "
"you met at the top of this chapter, subscribed to lifecycle phases:"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:174
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[plugins]\n"
"compliance = [\"post-build\"]    # SBOM (CycloneDX + SPDX) after a build\n"
"artifact   = [\"post-land\"]     # SLSA/in-toto provenance + cosign/minisign "
"signing\n"
"gate       = [\"pre-request\"]   # secret/hygiene gate blocks a bad PR "
"before it opens\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:181
msgid ""
"**SBOM** — a bill of materials (CycloneDX + SPDX) of what went into the "
"build."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:182
msgid "**Provenance** — SLSA/in-toto records of _how_ it was built and by whom."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:183
msgid ""
"**Signing** — cosign/minisign signatures so consumers can verify "
"authenticity."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:185
msgid ""
"And when someone asks \"what exactly shipped?\", `haw evidence` bundles the "
"manifest, the lock, the audit log, and status into one archive:"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/07-going-to-production.md:196
