#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:296
msgid "6. What MCP is, and why it matters here"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:298
msgid ""
"Before we write the MCP face, let's define MCP, because you can't wire up "
"what you don't understand."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:301
msgid ""
"**MCP (Model Context Protocol) is a standard way for an AI assistant to call "
"tools you expose.** In three sentences:"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:304
msgid ""
"It's a simple protocol spoken over stdio (standard input/output) using "
"JSON-RPC messages — your program reads requests on stdin and writes "
"responses on stdout."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:306
msgid ""
"Your program advertises a set of **tools** (named functions with typed "
"arguments), and an AI assistant like Claude can call them and read the "
"results."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:308
msgid ""
"That's it: MCP is the bridge that lets Claude _do things in your world_ — "
"read a diff, commit a repo — instead of only chatting about it."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:311
msgid ""
"**Why it matters here:** haw knows about your whole fleet — every repo, "
"every path, every changeset. If we expose that knowledge as MCP tools, "
"Claude can call them to read your diffs and write accurate commit messages "
"and PR text. Claude stops guessing and starts working from the real diff."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:316
msgid ""
"The good news: you don't implement the JSON-RPC wire protocol yourself. The "
"official MCP SDK ships a helper called **FastMCP** that turns a plain Python "
"function into a tool with one decorator. You write normal functions; FastMCP "
"handles the protocol."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:320
msgid "7. The MCP face: the tools Claude will call"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:322
msgid ""
"Here's the `run_mcp()` function. It imports FastMCP (failing gracefully if "
"the package isn't installed), creates a server, and registers each tool with "
"the `@mcp.tool()` decorator. The docstring of each function is what Claude "
"sees as the tool's description, so we write them clearly."
msgstr ""

