#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:646
msgid ""
"`draft_changeset_pr(title)` returns **one** PR body: the plugin assembles "
"the skeleton (per-repo sections plus a combined-summary slot), and **Claude "
"fills the prose** from the diffs. Dry by default; feed the result to `haw "
"change request` to open the linked PRs across the fleet."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:653
msgid ""
"**`write_commit` stays path-guarded.** There's no cross-repo \"write "
"everything\" tool by design — for a changeset you commit **per repo** "
"(Claude calls `write_commit` for each, each guarded to `root`), then run "
"`haw change request` to open the linked PRs across the fleet. Writes stay "
"small, reviewable, and inside your workspace."
