#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:704
msgid "14. Safety notes — this is the important bit"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:706
msgid ""
"Writing tools plus an LLM means guardrails matter. This is the section you "
"_don't_ skim. The plugin bakes the guardrails in:"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:709
msgid ""
"**Path-guarded writes.** `write_commit` and `draft_pr(submit=True)` refuse "
"any repo path that isn't inside the workspace `root` — Claude can't commit "
"outside your fleet."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:711
msgid ""
"**Dry by default.** `draft_pr` returns text only; it never pushes or "
"force-pushes unless you explicitly pass `submit=True`."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:713
msgid ""
"**No secrets in the plugin.** Forge authentication comes from _your_ "
"environment — haw's normal token resolution (`GITHUB_TOKEN`, and so on). The "
"plugin stores nothing."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:715
msgid ""
"**Separate process, honest exit codes.** The plugin runs out-of-process; a "
"bug can't crash haw, and a non-zero exit propagates so CI still gates."
msgstr ""

