#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:730
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:732
msgid ""
"**plugin** — an executable named `haw-<name>` on your `PATH`; haw runs it as "
"`haw <name>`."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:734
msgid ""
"**PATH dispatch** — the convention (shared with git/cargo/kubectl) where haw "
"runs an unknown subcommand by finding a matching executable on `PATH`."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:736
msgid ""
"**`haw.plugin/1`** — the JSON context haw hands every plugin (via `HAW_JSON` "
"or stdin), describing `root`, `stack`, and `repos`."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:738
msgid ""
"**`haw.plugin.report/1`** — the machine report a plugin prints for `--format "
"json`."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:739
msgid ""
"**`haw.plugin.view/1`** — the cockpit panel a plugin prints when haw asks it "
"to render (`HAW_RENDER=1`, `\"intent\": \"render\"`)."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:741
msgid ""
"**MCP (Model Context Protocol)** — a standard stdio JSON-RPC protocol that "
"lets an AI assistant call tools you expose."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:743
msgid ""
"**stdio** — a program's standard input and output streams; MCP messages "
"travel over them."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:744
msgid ""
"**tool** — a named function (with typed arguments) your MCP server "
"advertises for Claude to call."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:746
msgid ""
"**FastMCP** — the helper in the official MCP SDK that turns a Python "
"function into an MCP tool with a decorator."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:749
msgid "What you learned"
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:751
msgid ""
"A plugin is any executable named `haw-<name>` on `PATH`; haw hands it the "
"**`haw.plugin/1`** context via `$HAW_JSON` / stdin and propagates its exit "
"code."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:753
msgid ""
"It can print a **`haw.plugin.report/1`** (`--format json`) and a "
"**`haw.plugin.view/1`** panel (render intent, `HAW_RENDER=1`) for the "
"cockpit's Plugins view (`7`)."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:755
msgid ""
"MCP is a standard stdio protocol that lets Claude call tools you expose; the "
"same script becomes an **MCP server** with `--mcp`, using FastMCP."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:757
msgid ""
"**Level 1 (single repo)** teaches the protocol: `haw_context`, `repo_diff`, "
"`changeset_repos_tool`, `write_commit`, `draft_pr` — but Claude already sees "
"one repo natively."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:760
msgid ""
"**Level 2 (cross-repo)** is the real power: `changeset_diff` hands Claude "
"the _combined_ diff across the whole changeset, and `draft_changeset_pr` "
"gets it to write **one** fleet-wide PR narrative — the cross-repo story "
"neither Claude nor a single-repo tool can tell alone."
msgstr ""

#: ./learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:764
msgid ""
"**Guardrails:** path-guard writes to inside `root` (commit per repo, then "
"`haw change request`), keep PR drafting dry by default, and never store "
"secrets — auth stays in your environment."
msgstr ""

